This paper is about optimizing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for mobile devices, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on reducing the number of multiplies needed to perform convolutions, which is a key aspect of neural network optimization and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of network pruning and sparsity is also a common technique in neural network optimization, which could place this paper in the categories of neural networks (cs.NE) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
